    "body": "isn't that more or less what [this](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/IPython/config/configurable.py#L196) does ?\n\n```\n    @classmethod\n    def class_get_help(cls, inst=None):\n        \"\"\"Get the help string for this class in ReST format.\n\n        If `inst` is given, it's current trait values will be used in place of\n        class defaults.\n        \"\"\"\n```\n\nI would be in favor of refactoring the help-message generating mechanism to `return` instead of printing and re-use in [some places](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/IPython/config/configurable.py#L241).\nPotentially using a more-machine friendly format we can process hereafter.\n"
  },
